PN,44312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1780503064
OL,3,CWoman who alleges Jeffrey Donaldson
OL,4,Crape 'tried not to be a victim', court
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe barrister asked her if she
OL,8,Fremembered saying during this meeting
OL,9,Fthat Donaldson "hadn't made her
OL,10,Fcomfortable".
OL,12,FShe said she did not remember.
OL,14,FHe asked her if she remembered
OL,15,FDonaldson saying "if that was the way
OL,16,Fhe made her feel, then he apologised".
OL,18,FShe said: "The reason why he was there
OL,19,Fwas to apologise ... he pushed my legs
OL,20,Fapart, that is the truth of what had
OL,21,Fhappened."
OL,26,@qD@POUrD@LO]wD@ROUxD@eO]zD@KOU}D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/14
